                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7661/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-10-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Wilson states that in reference to his cable of September 10, Underwood’s
                    deviled ham, new analysis, shows no boric acid. Also states that ham at
                    custom-house will be admitted and that all future shipments will be admitted
                    subject to occasional analysis.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
